On Saturday, North Korea’s foreign minister informed the United Nations that the continuation of the sanctions deepened its distrust in the United States and that there was no possibility that his country would unilaterally renounce nuclear weapons under those circumstances.
Ri Yong Ho told the annual General Assembly of the international body that North Korea had taken “significant good-will measures” over the past year, such as stopping nuclear and missile tests, dismantling nuclear testing facilities and committing to non-proliferation of nuclear weapons and nuclear technology.
“However, we do not receive any similar response from the United States,” he said.
