Ri made no mention of plans for a second summit between Kim and Trump, announced by the U.S. leader at the United Nations earlier this week.
Instead, the minister highlighted three meetings held between Kim and Moon Jae, leader of South Korea, over the past five months, and added: "If South Korea had been interested in denuclearization instead of the United States, denuclearization of the Korean peninsula would not have been in a stagnation."
